  "prompt": "How does the law define illegal money laundering activities?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined in legal terms as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through a complex sequence of banking transfers or commercial transactions. Typically, it involves three key stages:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source of the money through complex transactions\n3. Integration: Merging the funds into legitimate economic activities\n\nMost jurisdictions consider money laundering a serious financial crime involving intentional concealment of the origins of illegally obtained money.",
